/*
 * Can you declare pointer to structure in c?
 */

/*
Explanation:
A pointer which is pointing to a structure is known as pointer to structure. Examples of pointers to structure:
What will be output if you will execute following code?
*/
#include<stdio.h>
struct address{
	char *name;
	char street[10];
	int pin;
}cus={"A.Kumar","H-2",456003},*p=&cus;

int main(){
	printf("%s %s",p->name,(*p).street);
	return 0;
}
/*
Output: A.Kumar H-2
Explanation:
p is pointer to structure address.-> and (*). Both are same thing. These operators are used to access data member of structure by using structureâ€™s pointer.
*/
